transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, good afternoon, John. Uh, you want my RX number or what do you need to...

Speaker 1: Uh, your, your, your name and zip code are the most helpful for me.

Speaker 2: Okay, it's Al Malone and, uh, 95, uh, what else did you want?

Speaker 1: 33321?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: 33321?

Speaker 2: 33321, yeah.

Speaker 1: Waterford Avenue?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: What can I help with today?

Speaker 2: First of all, they're not blue, like advertisement, and it doesn't say that on the pill, and it didn't work.

Speaker 1: Okay, so a few things. I can help you out here, sir, but a few things.

Speaker 2: We're called Score Blue. The AGV pill is not blue. It's a white pill.

Speaker 1: We advertise it as white. It's shown as white on the website.

Speaker 2: Um, but regarding it not working and that other stuff, do you have any pill?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'm sure you still have some pills, right?

Speaker 2: No, I have 10.

Speaker 1: Well, you were saying 20.

Speaker 2: I have 20 total.

Speaker 1: You haven't taken all 20?

Speaker 2: No, no, I only took the one.

Speaker 1: Oh, that's what I was asking. So can you, can you take out a pill and tell me what you see stamped on the pill?

Speaker 2: Sure, because I think there's a... Hang on one second, please.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay, it says...

Speaker 2: AC240.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: 340.

Speaker 1: So that's the problem, sir. We screwed up. Um, you didn't get sent the AGV.

Speaker 2: You were sent just regular, basic, generic Viagra, which is probably why it didn't work out well for you.

Speaker 1: So I'm going to, it's not going to cost you anything because you've already paid.

Speaker 2: I'm going to get your order fixed, though, sir. So I'm going to get you the right pill sent out and, um, they will say 100 on the pill.

Speaker 1: So when you said AC340, that's how I knew for sure it was the wrong thing.

Speaker 2: Yes, that's what I figured there was an error.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so I'm sorry about that, but you will get 20 of the right one, sir.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Welcome. Have a good one, Al.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
